evidence: "Qwind is a code that aims to simulate the launching and acceleration phase of line-driven winds in the context of AGN accretion discs." (domain-specific simulation application)
The repository is titled "Qwind.jl" and described as a code with documentation and installation instructions, implying users run it as an application rather than import it as a generic library.
"You can find the code documentation (with installation instructions) here" and the badges and links all point to the GitHub repository and its docs, indicating distribution via the source repo.
